Create directory in hdfs at given path:
hdfs dfs -mkdir /user/kct5thsemcdhid025/sample
-----------------------------------------------
List the controls of a directory:
hdfs dfs -ls /
---------------
Upload and download a file in HUpload:
hdfs dfs -put '/home/kct5thsemcdhid025/input.txt''/user/kct5thsemcdhid025/sample'
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Hadoop fs-get:
hdfs dfs -get '/user/kct5thsemcdhid025/matrix/Input''/home/kct5thsemcdhid025/'
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
See contents in file:
hdfs dfs -cat '/user/kct5thsemcdhid025/sample/*'
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
COpy a file from source to destination:
hdfs dfs -cp '/home/kct5thsemcdhid025/Input''/user/kct5thsemcdhid025/sample/'
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Copy a file from/Tolocal
hdfs dfs -copyFromLocal '/home/kct5thsemcdhid025/Input''/user/kct5thsemcdhid025/sample/'
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Copy Tolocal:
hdfs dfs -copyToLocal '/user/kct5thsemcdhid025/MATRIX/''/home/kct5thsemcdhid025/'
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Remove a file:
hdfs dfs -rm '/user/kct5thsemcdhid025/sample/input.txt'
-------------------------------------------------------
Display last few lines:
hdfs dfs -tail '/user/kct5thsemcdhid025/sample/Input/Input.txt'
---------------------------------------------------------------
Display the aggregate length of a file:
hdfs dfs -du '/user/kct5thsemcdhid025/sample/Input/Input.txt'
